  "comment": "[gof-patterns]  Embedding providers — convert text to vectors for semantic search.\n\n Provides:\n   - EmbeddingProvider  vtable interface\n   - NoopEmbedding      returns empty vectors (keyword-only fallback)\n   - OllamaEmbedding    Ollama local /api/embed endpoint\n   - OpenAiEmbedding    OpenAI-compatible /v1/embeddings endpoint\n   - createEmbeddingProvider() factory",
  "detail": "## Module Purpose and Architecture\n\nThis module implements a flexible embedding provider system for semantic search applications in Zig. It provides a clean interface for converting text into vector embeddings, supporting multiple backend services including local Ollama instances and OpenAI-compatible APIs.\n\nThe architecture follows a strategy pattern with a vtable-based interface (similar to Rust's trait objects), allowing runtime polymorphism while maintaining compile-time type safety where possible. The module delegates common concerns like URL validation and JSON escaping to shared utilities in `src/common/`, promoting code reuse across the application.\n\n## Key Abstractions and Relationships\n\n**EmbeddingProvider**: A vtable-based interface that defines the contract for all embedding providers. It exposes three core operations:\n- `getName()`: Identifies the provider type at runtime\n- `getDimensions()`: Returns the vector dimensionality\n- `embed()`: Converts text to float32 vectors\n- `deinit()`: Cleans up resources\n\n**NoopEmbedding**: A null-object pattern implementation that returns empty vectors. This serves as a safe fallback when no embedding service is available, allowing keyword-only search functionality without breaking existing code.\n\n**OllamaEmbedding**: Wraps the local Ollama `/api/embed` endpoint. It maintains configuration (base URL, model name, dimensions) and handles HTTP communication with automatic response parsing via `parseOllamaResponse()`.\n\n**OpenAiEmbedding**: Provides compatibility with OpenAI's `/v1/embeddings` API standard, enabling integration with various cloud providers that follow the same specification.\n\n## Public API and Usage Patterns\n\nThe public API exposes both type definitions and utility functions:\n\n```zig\n// Factory pattern for provider creation\nconst provider = createEmbeddingProvider(allocator, \"ollama\", null, \"nomic-embed-text\", 768);\n\n// Type-safe interface usage\nconst dims = provider.getDimensions();\nconst vector = try provider.embed(allocator, text);\n\n// Null-safety with Noop fallback\nconst noop = NoopEmbedding.provider(self);\n```\n\nThe module also provides two response parsers as public utilities:\n- `parseOllamaResponse()`: Converts Ollama JSON responses to float32 vectors\n- `parseOpenAiResponse()`: Handles OpenAI-compatible embedding formats\n\n## Important Implementation Details\n\n1. **Memory Management**: The vtable pattern requires careful pointer casting using `@ptrCast` and `@alignCast`. Each provider instance owns its allocator, ensuring proper cleanup via the `deinit()` method.\n\n2. **URL Validation**: Before establishing connections, providers validate URLs against HTTPS or localhost HTTP protocols using `common.validateHttpsOrLocalHttp()`, preventing accidental external network access.\n\n3. **Default Configuration**: OllamaEmbedding provides sensible defaults (localhost:11434, nomic-embed-text model, 768 dimensions) that can be overridden at initialization time.\n\n4. **Allocator Safety**: All operations respect Zig's allocator protocol, with proper error handling via `errdefer` to prevent memory leaks during initialization failures.\n\n## Design Patterns Used\n\n- **VTable/Interface Pattern**: Enables runtime polymorphism while maintaining type safety\n- **Factory Method**: Centralizes provider creation logic in `createEmbeddingProvider()`\n- **Null Object Pattern**: NoopEmbedding provides a safe default that doesn't break functionality\n- **Dependency Injection**: Providers receive allocators and configuration externally, enabling testing and flexibility",
  "keywords": ["EmbeddingProvider", "OllamaEmbedding", "OpenAiEmbedding", "semantic search", "vtable interface", "strategy pattern", "factory method", "vector embeddings", "NoopEmbedding", "parseOllamaResponse"],
